,"order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"> Place a 100mL beaker containing approximately<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">in the chaber next to the petri dish of seeds.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bc55a.jpeg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"067180F030B011E983E69B371425768E","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":50,"unit":"ml","title":"bleach"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"69247F22A0C94DFDB165E952AF83404B","order_id":3,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bc55a.jpeg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":708593,"guid":"23129AF030B011E983E69B371425768E","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D1E9191E36904DE38FFAF4F26B9BE9DE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"84C61D6A558D447A8C5119E2A0ADCEF0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">In a fume hood, place an empty dessication chamber with a petri dish of the seeds you wish to surface sterilize. Leave the lid of the petri dish halfway on, so that you can quickly close it later.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"B2A02AC8E557463D8624FC4B67CF7106","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">A dessication chamber per se is not necessary; you simply need some container to hold the gas for a few hours. It does not need to be thoroughly airtight, but it helps.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">If you plan to sterilize multiple genotypes of seeds, be aware that the gas produced will erase most markers. Pencil and paper labels work well though.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":708595,"guid":"B7766DC030B011E983E69B371425768E","previous_id":708592,"previous_guid":"E7E8BB3030AF11E983E69B371425768E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7884AB689AE340479E2CBE8F83C60848","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F0CA5DA97D8642BA91776F76E57DFE99","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare approximately <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">in a transfer pipet or similar.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"0831D92030B111E983E69B371425768E","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":3,"unit":"ml","title":"HCl"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":708597,"guid":"19ACF22030B111E983E69B371425768E","previous_id":708595,"previous_guid":"B7766DC030B011E983E69B371425768E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9FF1B6E8AE4444188EDD18E6F80B764A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"89EC3BA2754C4064945453AED4432CA0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The following steps must occur quickly to prevent the escape of the gas. Hold the lid to the chamber in one hand. With the other hand squirt the HCl into the beaker of bleach and quickly close the chamber to seal in the gas. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"7F4108975FEC40DF82F8CADBDE8380EF","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The HCl and the bleach will react violently to produce the gas, do not be startled. The larger beaker should prevent any bubbles of bleach or HCl from contacting the rest of the set up.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":708601,"guid":"BDB3C29030B111E983E69B371425768E","previous_id":708597,"previous_guid":"19ACF22030B111E983E69B371425768E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E98609CF8A4343318514120427350523","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4E24680144CF486D8E05157742217920","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Allow the seeds to be sterilized for approximately 3 hours. This time works for tomato, tobacco, and Arabidopsis seeds. The seeds may become whiter in color, this is also normal and does not seem to affect germination rates.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":708602,"guid":"EFFB9DE030B111E983E69B371425768E","previous_id":708601,"previous_guid":"BDB3C29030B111E983E69B371425768E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"37FE7A0689AF4AA3A23CA5CBCC328614","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F7DF5A3BA9F641D7AF0414C581FA7062","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Once the time is up, quickly open the chamber and slide the lid completely onto the petri dish to seal it. The seeds can be stored like this for several weeks or transfered to a laminar flow hood for further use. Allow the chmaber to air out for an hour or so.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":708603,"guid":"09D7A47030B211E983E69B371425768E","previous_id":708602,"previous_guid":"EFFB9DE030B111E983E69B371425768E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7699E7E624354D158F1A5FBBB1F581F1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C79A80049E4841B3A6C4CCD230D999D4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">If the reaction of the bleach and HCl went to perfect completion, the beaker should only contain salt water. In reality it is likely acidic. Dispose of this according to your local regulations.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null}],"materials":[{"id":1998,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Petri Dish","linfor":null,"url":"http:\/\/store.p212121.com\/petri-dishes\/","sku":"LI-PD01100","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"P212121","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/store.p212121.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/7.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/7.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":7},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":3566,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Hydrochloric Acid","linfor":null,"url":"","sku":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Contributed by users","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":1},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":4704,"mol_weight":0,"name":"